700926f-a.text:
View 1: East Tremont Avenue at the north-west cor. White Plains Road, Bronx, showing the White Plains Road bridge over the New Haven Railroad tracks.
View 2: White Plains Road and East Tremont Avenue, north-east corner, showing the Unionport Road bridge over the tracks. The gasoline station occupies a triangular plot between
the two thoroughfares.
Sept. 4, 1939
P. L. Sperr, photographer

701572f-c.text:
(view 1) White Plains Road at East Iremont Avene looking south eastward and showing construction of the Parkchester Houses, on the former site of the Catholic Protectory. (view 2) White Plains Road and Westchester Avenue, Bronx, looking south eastward and showing construction of the
Parkchester Houses.
(view 3) Castle Hill Avenue at St. Raymond Avenue, Sronx, looking north westward and showing construction of Parkchester Houses.
(view 4) Castle Hill Avenue, opposite Glover Street, Bronx, locking north westward and showing construction of the
Parkchester Houses.
P. L. Sperr, photographer
September 4, 1939
